{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01VtzVbYhW3ar5YzcwbeWA8k","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create all the Spring Boot files. I'll use a general-purpose agent to write all the files in one go:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":170,"cache_read_input_tokens":114767,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":170,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2651},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f1542671-6929-49f9-9925-fcf6260de3ab","uuid":"b208331f-435c-432a-b2ab-c8cf9a5dba53"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01VtzVbYhW3ar5YzcwbeWA8k","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01WjnxDpGTxVv7YaJZqQuaGb","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Write all Spring Boot Java files","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE petclinic application to Spring Boot. I need you to create all the following Java files. The base path for all files is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/woehlke/jakartaee/petclinic/\n\nThe application has these entities:\n- Owner (fields: id, uuid, searchindex, firstName, lastName, address, houseNumber, addressInfo, city, zipCode, phoneNumber, email)\n- Pet (fields: id, uuid, searchindex, birthDate, name, type->PetType, owner->Owner)\n- PetType (fields: id, uuid, searchindex, name)\n- Specialty (fields: id, uuid, searchindex, name)\n- Vet (fields: id, uuid, searchindex, firstName, lastName, specialties->Set<Specialty>)\n- Visit (fields: id, uuid, searchindex, date, description, pet->Pet)\n\nThe original Jakarta EE app used:\n- @Entity, @Table, @NamedQueries, @EntityListeners, @SequenceGenerator\n- @Stateless EJBs for services\n- @EJB injection\n- JAX-RS @Path endpoints\n- JSF views (we're dropping these)\n- PostgreSQL database\n\nFor Spring Boot 3.2.x, create these files using the Write tool:\n\n## 1. PetclinicApplication.java (main Spring Boot app class)\nPackage: org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic\n- @SpringBootApplication\n- Standard main method\n- Context path /petclinic set in application.properties\n\n## 2. Entity files (keep jakarta.persistence annotations, remove EJB/CDI)\n\n### Owner.java \n- Keep @Entity, @Table, @NamedQueries (they work in Spring Boot 3), @Column, @Id, @GeneratedValue, @SequenceGenerator\n- Keep @UniqueConstraint\n- Keep Lombok annotations\n- Keep validation annotations (jakarta.validation)\n- Remove @EntityListeners (simplify)\n- Table name: \"owner\", sequence: owner_seq\n- Fields: id (Long), uuid (UUID), searchindex (String), firstName, lastName, address, houseNumber, addressInfo, city, zipCode, phoneNumber, email\n\n### Pet.java\n- Table name: \"owner_pet\", sequence: owner_pet_seq\n- @ManyToOne to PetType and Owner\n- Fields: id, uuid, searchindex, birthDate (Date with @Temporal(DATE)), name, type (PetType), owner (Owner)\n\n### PetType.java\n- Table name: \"owner_pet_pettype\", sequence: owner_pet_pettype_seq\n- Fields: id, uuid, searchindex, name\n\n### Specialty.java\n- Table name: \"specialty\", sequence: specialty_seq\n- Fields: id, uuid, searchindex, name\n\n### Vet.java\n- Table name: \"vet\", sequence: vet_seq\n- @ManyToMany to Specialty via join table \"vet_specialties\"\n- Fields: id, uuid, searchindex, firstName, lastName, specialties (Set<Specialty>)\n\n### Visit.java\n- Table name: \"owner_pet_visit\", sequence: owner_pet_visit_seq\n- @ManyToOne to Pet\n- Fields: id, uuid, searchindex, date (Date with @Temporal(DATE)), description, pet (Pet)\n\n## 3. Spring Data JPA Repository interfaces\n\n### OwnerRepository.java (in owner.db package)\n- extends JpaRepository<Owner, Long>\n- @Query for search: \"select o from Owner o where o.searchindex like :searchterm order by o.lastName,o.firstName asc\"\n- findAll ordered by lastName, firstName\n\n### PetRepository.java (in pet.db package)\n- extends JpaRepository<Pet, Long>\n- List<Pet> findByOwnerOrderByNameAsc(Owner owner)\n\n### PetTypeRepository.java (in pettype.db package)\n- extends JpaRepository<PetType, Long>\n- findAllByOrderByNameAsc()\n\n### SpecialtyRepository.java (in specialty.db package)\n- extends JpaRepository<Specialty, Long>\n- search by searchindex like\n- findAllByOrderByNameAsc()\n\n### VetRepository.java (in vet.db package)\n- extends JpaRepository<Vet, Long>\n- search by searchindex like\n- findAllByOrderByLastNameAscFirstNameAsc()\n\n### VisitRepository.java (in visit.db package)\n- extends JpaRepository<Visit, Long>\n- List<Visit> findByPetOrderByDateAsc(Pet pet)\n\n## 4. Service interfaces and implementations\n\n### OwnerService.java + OwnerServiceImpl.java (in owner.db package)\n- @Service + @Transactional\n- Inject OwnerRepository, PetRepository, VisitRepository\n- Methods: getAll(), findById(long), addNew(Owner), update(Owner), delete(long), search(String), getPetsAsList(Owner), addNewVisit(Visit)\n- In addNew: set uuid = UUID.randomUUID()\n\n### PetTypeService.java + PetTypeServiceImpl.java (in pettype.db package)\n- @Service + @Transactional\n- Methods: getAll(), findById(long), addNew(PetType), update(PetType), delete(long), search(String)\n\n### SpecialtyService.java + SpecialtyServiceImpl.java (in specialty.db package)\n- Same pattern as PetType\n\n### VetService.java + VetServiceImpl.java (in vet.db package)\n- Same pattern + methods for specialty management\n\n### VisitService.java + VisitServiceImpl.java (in visit.db package)\n- Methods: getAll(), findById(long), addNew(Visit), update(Visit), delete(long), getVisits(Pet)\n\n## 5. DTO classes (keep them simple, use Jackson annotations instead of JAXB/JSON-B)\n\n### OwnerDto.java (in owner.api package)\n- Plain POJO with Jackson @JsonProperty or just public fields\n- Fields: id, uuid, firstName, lastName, address, houseNumber, addressInfo, city, zipCode, phoneNumber, petList (List<PetDto>)\n\n### PetDto.java (in pet.api package)\n- Fields: id, uuid, name, birthDate, petTypeId, petTypeName\n\n### PetTypeDto.java (in pettype.api package)\n- Fields: id, uuid, name\n\n### SpecialtyDto.java (in specialty.api package)\n- Fields: id, uuid, name\n\n### VetDto.java (in vet.api package)\n- Fields: id, uuid, firstName, lastName, specialties (List<SpecialtyDto>)\n\n### VisitDto.java (in visit.api package)\n- Fields: id, uuid, date, description, petId, petName\n\n## 6. REST Controllers (Spring MVC replacing JAX-RS)\n\n### OwnerController.java (in owner package)\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/owner\")\n- @GetMapping(\"/list\") -> List<OwnerDto>\n- @GetMapping(\"/{id}\") -> OwnerDto\n\n### PetTypeController.java (in pettype package)\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/petType\")\n- @GetMapping(\"/list\") -> List<PetTypeDto>\n- @GetMapping(\"/{id}\") -> PetTypeDto\n\n### SpecialtyController.java (in specialty package)\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/specialty\")\n- @GetMapping(\"/list\") -> List<SpecialtyDto>\n- @GetMapping(\"/{id}\") -> SpecialtyDto\n\n### VetController.java (in vet package)\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/vet\")\n- @GetMapping(\"/list\") -> List<VetDto>\n- @GetMapping(\"/{id}\") -> VetDto\n\n### VisitController.java (in visit package)\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/visit\")\n- @GetMapping(\"/list\") -> List<VisitDto>\n- @GetMapping(\"/{id}\") -> VisitDto\n\n## 7. Utility/Converter classes\n\n### OwnerEndpointUtil.java (in owner.api package)\n- @Component\n- Convert Owner to OwnerDto and List<Owner> to List<OwnerDto>\n- Inject PetRepository to get pets for each owner\n\n### PetEndpointUtil.java (in pet.api package)\n- @Component\n- Convert Pet to PetDto\n\n### PetTypeEndpointUtil.java (in pettype.api package)\n- @Component \n- Convert PetType to PetTypeDto\n\n### SpecialtyEndpointUtil.java (in specialty.api package)\n- @Component\n- Convert Specialty to SpecialtyDto\n\n### VetEndpointUtil.java (in vet.api package)\n- @Component\n- Convert Vet to VetDto (include specialty list)\n\n### VisitEndpointUtil.java (in visit.api package)\n- @Component\n- Convert Visit to VisitDto\n\nIMPORTANT RULES:\n1. All entities must keep their exact table names and column names from the original (for data.sql compatibility)\n2. jakarta.persistence.* imports are correct for Spring Boot 3.x\n3. jakarta.validation.* imports are correct for Spring Boot 3.x\n4. Use @Transactional from org.springframework.transaction.annotation\n5. Use @Service from org.springframework.stereotype\n6. Use @Component from org.springframework.stereotype\n7. Use @RestController, @RequestMapping, @GetMapping, @PathVariable from org.springframework.web.bind.annotation\n8. Use @Autowired or constructor injection\n9. Remove ALL EJB imports (jakarta.ejb.*), CDI imports (jakarta.enterprise.*, jakarta.inject.*), JSF imports (jakarta.faces.*), JAX-RS imports (jakarta.ws.rs.*)\n10. Remove ALL JSF View classes, FlowView classes, Converter classes (JSF-specific)\n11. Keep Lombok @Getter, @Setter, @ToString, @NoArgsConstructor, @AllArgsConstructor, @Log\n12. Keep Serializable interface on entities\n\nWrite ALL the files listed above using the Write tool. Create any necessary directories first."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":170,"cache_read_input_tokens":114767,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":170,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2651},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f1542671-6929-49f9-9925-fcf6260de3ab","uuid":"c628a65b-486b-4da7-ab29-925b8ece9512"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE petclinic application to Spring Boot. I need you to create all the following Java files. The base path for all files is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/woehlke/jakartaee/petclinic/\n\nThe application has these entities:\n- Owner (fields: id, uuid, searchindex, firstName, lastName, address, houseNumber, addressInfo, city, zipCode, phoneNumber, email)\n- Pet (fields: id, uuid, searchindex, birthDate, name, type->PetType, owner->Owner)\n- PetType (fields: id, uuid, searchindex, name)\n- Specialty (fields: id, uuid, searchindex, name)\n- Vet (fields: id, uuid, searchindex, firstName, lastName, specialties->Set<Specialty>)\n- Visit (fields: id, uuid, searchindex, date, description, pet->Pet)\n\nThe original Jakarta EE app used:\n- @Entity, @Table, @NamedQueries, @EntityListeners, @SequenceGenerator\n- @Stateless EJBs for services\n- @EJB injection\n- JAX-RS @Path endpoints\n- JSF views (we're dropping these)\n- PostgreSQL database\n\nFor Spring Boot 3.2.x, create these files using the Write tool:\n\n## 1. PetclinicApplication.java (main Spring Boot app class)\nPackage: org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic\n- @SpringBootApplication\n- Standard main method\n- Context path /petclinic set in application.properties\n\n## 2. Entity files (keep jakarta.persistence annotations, remove EJB/CDI)\n\n### Owner.java \n- Keep @Entity, @Table, @NamedQueries (they work in Spring Boot 3), @Column, @Id, @GeneratedValue, @SequenceGenerator\n- Keep @UniqueConstraint\n- Keep Lombok annotations\n- Keep validation annotations (jakarta.validation)\n- Remove @EntityListeners (simplify)\n- Table name: \"owner\", sequence: owner_seq\n- Fields: id (Long), uuid (UUID), searchindex (String), firstName, lastName, address, houseNumber, addressInfo, city, zipCode, phoneNumber, email\n\n### Pet.java\n- Table name: \"owner_pet\", sequence: owner_pet_seq\n- @ManyToOne to PetType and Owner\n- Fields: id, uuid, searchindex, birthDate (Date with @Temporal(DATE)), name, type (PetType), owner (Owner)\n\n### PetType.java\n- Table name: \"owner_pet_pettype\", sequence: owner_pet_pettype_seq\n- Fields: id, uuid, searchindex, name\n\n### Specialty.java\n- Table name: \"specialty\", sequence: specialty_seq\n- Fields: id, uuid, searchindex, name\n\n### Vet.java\n- Table name: \"vet\", sequence: vet_seq\n- @ManyToMany to Specialty via join table \"vet_specialties\"\n- Fields: id, uuid, searchindex, firstName, lastName, specialties (Set<Specialty>)\n\n### Visit.java\n- Table name: \"owner_pet_visit\", sequence: owner_pet_visit_seq\n- @ManyToOne to Pet\n- Fields: id, uuid, searchindex, date (Date with @Temporal(DATE)), description, pet (Pet)\n\n## 3. Spring Data JPA Repository interfaces\n\n### OwnerRepository.java (in owner.db package)\n- extends JpaRepository<Owner, Long>\n- @Query for search: \"select o from Owner o where o.searchindex like :searchterm order by o.lastName,o.firstName asc\"\n- findAll ordered by lastName, firstName\n\n### PetRepository.java (in pet.db package)\n- extends JpaRepository<Pet, Long>\n- List<Pet> findByOwnerOrderByNameAsc(Owner owner)\n\n### PetTypeRepository.java (in pettype.db package)\n- extends JpaRepository<PetType, Long>\n- findAllByOrderByNameAsc()\n\n### SpecialtyRepository.java (in specialty.db package)\n- extends JpaRepository<Specialty, Long>\n- search by searchindex like\n- findAllByOrderByNameAsc()\n\n### VetRepository.java (in vet.db package)\n- extends JpaRepository<Vet, Long>\n- search by searchindex like\n- findAllByOrderByLastNameAscFirstNameAsc()\n\n### VisitRepository.java (in visit.db package)\n- extends JpaRepository<Visit, Long>\n- List<Visit> findByPetOrderByDateAsc(Pet pet)\n\n## 4. Service interfaces and implementations\n\n### OwnerService.java + OwnerServiceImpl.java (in owner.db package)\n- @Service + @Transactional\n- Inject OwnerRepository, PetRepository, VisitRepository\n- Methods: getAll(), findById(long), addNew(Owner), update(Owner), delete(long), search(String), getPetsAsList(Owner), addNewVisit(Visit)\n- In addNew: set uuid = UUID.randomUUID()\n\n### PetTypeService.java + PetTypeServiceImpl.java (in pettype.db package)\n- @Service + @Transactional\n- Methods: getAll(), findById(long), addNew(PetType), update(PetType), delete(long), search(String)\n\n### SpecialtyService.java + SpecialtyServiceImpl.java (in specialty.db package)\n- Same pattern as PetType\n\n### VetService.java + VetServiceImpl.java (in vet.db package)\n- Same pattern + methods for specialty management\n\n### VisitService.java + VisitServiceImpl.java (in visit.db package)\n- Methods: getAll(), findById(long), addNew(Visit), update(Visit), delete(long), getVisits(Pet)\n\n## 5. DTO classes (keep them simple, use Jackson annotations instead of JAXB/JSON-B)\n\n### OwnerDto.java (in owner.api package)\n- Plain POJO with Jackson @JsonProperty or just public fields\n- Fields: id, uuid, firstName, lastName, address, houseNumber, addressInfo, city, zipCode, phoneNumber, petList (List<PetDto>)\n\n### PetDto.java (in pet.api package)\n- Fields: id, uuid, name, birthDate, petTypeId, petTypeName\n\n### PetTypeDto.java (in pettype.api package)\n- Fields: id, uuid, name\n\n### SpecialtyDto.java (in specialty.api package)\n- Fields: id, uuid, name\n\n### VetDto.java (in vet.api package)\n- Fields: id, uuid, firstName, lastName, specialties (List<SpecialtyDto>)\n\n### VisitDto.java (in visit.api package)\n- Fields: id, uuid, date, description, petId, petName\n\n## 6. REST Controllers (Spring MVC replacing JAX-RS)\n\n### OwnerController.java (in owner package)\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/owner\")\n- @GetMapping(\"/list\") -> List<OwnerDto>\n- @GetMapping(\"/{id}\") -> OwnerDto\n\n### PetTypeController.java (in pettype package)\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/petType\")\n- @GetMapping(\"/list\") -> List<PetTypeDto>\n- @GetMapping(\"/{id}\") -> PetTypeDto\n\n### SpecialtyController.java (in specialty package)\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/specialty\")\n- @GetMapping(\"/list\") -> List<SpecialtyDto>\n- @GetMapping(\"/{id}\") -> SpecialtyDto\n\n### VetController.java (in vet package)\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/vet\")\n- @GetMapping(\"/list\") -> List<VetDto>\n- @GetMapping(\"/{id}\") -> VetDto\n\n### VisitController.java (in visit package)\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/visit\")\n- @GetMapping(\"/list\") -> List<VisitDto>\n- @GetMapping(\"/{id}\") -> VisitDto\n\n## 7. Utility/Converter classes\n\n### OwnerEndpointUtil.java (in owner.api package)\n- @Component\n- Convert Owner to OwnerDto and List<Owner> to List<OwnerDto>\n- Inject PetRepository to get pets for each owner\n\n### PetEndpointUtil.java (in pet.api package)\n- @Component\n- Convert Pet to PetDto\n\n### PetTypeEndpointUtil.java (in pettype.api package)\n- @Component \n- Convert PetType to PetTypeDto\n\n### SpecialtyEndpointUtil.java (in specialty.api package)\n- @Component\n- Convert Specialty to SpecialtyDto\n\n### VetEndpointUtil.java (in vet.api package)\n- @Component\n- Convert Vet to VetDto (include specialty list)\n\n### VisitEndpointUtil.java (in visit.api package)\n- @Component\n- Convert Visit to VisitDto\n\nIMPORTANT RULES:\n1. All entities must keep their exact table names and column names from the original (for data.sql compatibility)\n2. jakarta.persistence.* imports are correct for Spring Boot 3.x\n3. jakarta.validation.* imports are correct for Spring Boot 3.x\n4. Use @Transactional from org.springframework.transaction.annotation\n5. Use @Service from org.springframework.stereotype\n6. Use @Component from org.springframework.stereotype\n7. Use @RestController, @RequestMapping, @GetMapping, @PathVariable from org.springframework.web.bind.annotation\n8. Use @Autowired or constructor injection\n9. Remove ALL EJB imports (jakarta.ejb.*), CDI imports (jakarta.enterprise.*, jakarta.inject.*), JSF imports (jakarta.faces.*), JAX-RS imports (jakarta.ws.rs.*)\n10. Remove ALL JSF View classes, FlowView classes, Converter classes (JSF-specific)\n11. Keep Lombok @Getter, @Setter, @ToString, @NoArgsConstructor, @AllArgsConstructor, @Log\n12. Keep Serializable interface on entities\n\nWrite ALL the files listed above using the Write tool. Create any necessary directories first."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WjnxDpGTxVv7YaJZqQuaGb","session_id":"f1542671-6929-49f9-9925-fcf6260de3ab","uuid":"cfc6e8dc-0449-4d5f-882e-3e0d27ff441d"}
