{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WjnxDpGTxVv7YaJZqQuaGb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Migration Complete - Summary\n\nI have successfully created all 40 Java files for migrating the Jakarta EE petclinic application to Spring Boot 3.2.x. Here's what was created:\n\n### 1. Main Application Class (1 file)\n- **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/woehlke/jakartaee/petclinic/PetclinicApplication.java**\n\n### 2. Entity Classes (6 files)\nAll entities maintain exact table names and column names from the original Jakarta EE application for data.sql compatibility:\n- **Owner.java** - Table: owner, Sequence: owner_seq\n- **Pet.java** - Table: owner_pet, Sequence: owner_pet_seq\n- **PetType.java** - Table: owner_pet_pettype, Sequence: owner_pet_pettype_seq\n- **Specialty.java** - Table: specialty, Sequence: specialty_seq\n- **Vet.java** - Table: vet, Sequence: vet_seq (with ManyToMany to Specialty)\n- **Visit.java** - Table: owner_pet_visit, Sequence: owner_pet_visit_seq\n\n### 3. Spring Data JPA Repositories (6 files)\n- **OwnerRepository.java** - with custom search query\n- **PetRepository.java** - findByOwnerOrderByNameAsc\n- **PetTypeRepository.java** - findAllByOrderByNameAsc\n- **SpecialtyRepository.java** - with search and ordering\n- **VetRepository.java** - with search and ordering\n- **VisitRepository.java** - findByPetOrderByDateAsc\n\n### 4. Service Interfaces and Implementations (12 files)\n- **OwnerService.java** + **OwnerServiceImpl.java**\n- **PetTypeService.java** + **PetTypeServiceImpl.java**\n- **SpecialtyService.java** + **SpecialtyServiceImpl.java**\n- **VetService.java** + **VetServiceImpl.java** (includes specialty management)\n- **VisitService.java** + **VisitServiceImpl.java**\n\nAll services use:\n- @Service annotation\n- @Transactional from Spring\n- Constructor injection with @Autowired\n- UUID auto-generation in addNew methods\n\n### 5. DTO Classes (6 files)\nUsing Jackson annotations for JSON serialization:\n- **OwnerDto.java** - includes petList\n- **PetDto.java** - includes petTypeId and petTypeName\n- **PetTypeDto.java**\n- **SpecialtyDto.java**\n- **VetDto.java** - includes specialties list\n- **VisitDto.java** - includes petId and petName\n\n### 6. REST Controllers (5 files)\nUsing Spring MVC (replacing JAX-RS):\n- **OwnerController.java** - @RequestMapping(\"/rest/owner\")\n- **PetTypeController.java** - @RequestMapping(\"/rest/petType\")\n- **SpecialtyController.java** - @RequestMapping(\"/rest/specialty\")\n- **VetController.java** - @RequestMapping(\"/rest/vet\")\n- **VisitController.java** - @RequestMapping(\"/rest/visit\")\n\nAll controllers provide:\n- GET /list - returns all entities as DTOs\n- GET /{id} - returns single entity by ID as DTO\n\n### 7. Converter/Utility Classes (6 files)\nAll marked with @Component for Spring injection:\n- **OwnerEndpointUtil.java** - converts Owner to OwnerDto (includes pets)\n- **PetEndpointUtil.java** - converts Pet to PetDto\n- **PetTypeEndpointUtil.java** - converts PetType to PetTypeDto\n- **SpecialtyEndpointUtil.java** - converts Specialty to SpecialtyDto\n- **VetEndpointUtil.java** - converts Vet to VetDto (includes specialties)\n- **VisitEndpointUtil.java** - converts Visit to VisitDto\n\n### Key Migration Features\n\n1. **Removed all Jakarta EE specific dependencies:**\n   - No @EJB, @Stateless (replaced with @Service)\n   - No JAX-RS @Path, @GET (replaced with @RestController, @GetMapping)\n   - No CDI @Inject (replaced with @Autowired)\n   - No JSF components\n\n2. **Kept Spring Boot 3.x compatible annotations:**\n   - jakarta.persistence.* (JPA annotations work in Spring Boot 3.x)\n   - jakarta.validation.* (Bean Validation works in Spring Boot 3.x)\n   - Lombok annotations (@Getter, @Setter, @ToString, @NoArgsConstructor, @AllArgsConstructor, @Log)\n\n3. **Used Spring Framework annotations:**\n   - @SpringBootApplication\n   - @Service, @Component, @Repository\n   - @Transactional (from org.springframework.transaction.annotation)\n   - @RestController, @RequestMapping, @GetMapping, @PathVariable\n   - @Autowired for dependency injection\n\n4. **Maintained database compatibility:**\n   - All table names preserved exactly\n   - All column names preserved exactly\n   - All sequence names preserved exactly\n   - @SequenceGenerator with allocationSize = 1\n\n5. **Entity lifecycle callbacks:**\n   - @PrePersist and @PreUpdate methods for searchindex population\n   - UUID auto-generation in service layer\n\nAll files have been created in the correct package structure and are ready for use with Spring Boot 3.2.x!"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f1542671-6929-49f9-9925-fcf6260de3ab","uuid":"dbd9c89e-7427-41a8-9199-c990d3be96d2"}
