{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012ZdmFpMMUpoGYfJeEerJ6d","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.db;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Pattern;\n     6→import lombok.*;\n     7→\n     8→import java.io.Serializable;\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Entity\n    12→@Table(\n    13→    name = \"owner\",\n    14→    uniqueConstraints = {\n    15→        @UniqueConstraint(name = \"ux_owner_uuid\", columnNames = {\"uuid\"})\n    16→    }\n    17→)\n    18→@NamedQueries({\n    19→    @NamedQuery(\n    20→        name = \"Owner.getAll\",\n    21→        query = \"select o from Owner o order by o.lastName, o.firstName\"\n    22→    ),\n    23→    @NamedQuery(\n    24→        name = \"Owner.searchIndex\",\n    25→        query = \"select o from Owner o where o.searchindex like :searchterm order by o.lastName, o.firstName\"\n    26→    )\n    27→})\n    28→@Getter\n    29→@Setter\n    30→@ToString\n    31→@NoArgsConstructor\n    32→@AllArgsConstructor\n    33→public class Owner implements Serializable {\n    34→\n    35→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    36→\n    37→    @Id\n    38→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.SEQUENCE, generator = \"owner_seq\")\n    39→    @SequenceGenerator(name = \"owner_seq\", sequenceName = \"owner_seq\", allocationSize = 1)\n    40→    private Long id;\n    41→\n    42→    @Column(name = \"uuid\", nullable = false, unique = true)\n    43→    private UUID uuid;\n    44→\n    45→    @Column(name = \"searchindex\", length = 1024)\n    46→    private String searchindex;\n    47→\n    48→    @NotBlank\n    49→    @Column(name = \"first_name\", nullable = false)\n    50→    private String firstName;\n    51→\n    52→    @NotBlank\n    53→    @Column(name = \"last_name\", nullable = false)\n    54→    private String lastName;\n    55→\n    56→    @NotBlank\n    57→    @Column(name = \"address\", nullable = false)\n    58→    private String address;\n    59→\n    60→    @NotBlank\n    61→    @Column(name = \"house_number\", nullable = false)\n    62→    private String houseNumber;\n    63→\n    64→    @Column(name = \"address_info\")\n    65→    private String addressInfo;\n    66→\n    67→    @NotBlank\n    68→    @Column(name = \"city\", nullable = false)\n    69→    private String city;\n    70→\n    71→    @NotBlank\n    72→    @Pattern(regexp = \"^[0-9]{5}$\")\n    73→    @Column(name = \"zip_code\", nullable = false, length = 5)\n    74→    private String zipCode;\n    75→\n    76→    @NotBlank\n    77→    @Column(name = \"phone_number\", nullable = false)\n    78→    private String phoneNumber;\n    79→\n    80→    @Column(name = \"email\")\n    81→    private String email;\n    82→\n    83→    @PrePersist\n    84→    @PreUpdate\n    85→    public void prePersist() {\n    86→        this.searchindex = (this.firstName + \" \" + this.lastName + \" \" +\n    87→                           this.address + \" \" + this.houseNumber + \" \" +\n    88→                           (this.addressInfo != null ? this.addressInfo + \" \" : \"\") +\n    89→                           this.city + \" \" + this.zipCode + \" \" +\n    90→                           this.phoneNumber + \" \" +\n    91→                           (this.email != null ? this.email : \"\")).toLowerCase();\n    92→    }\n    93→}\n    94→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f1542671-6929-49f9-9925-fcf6260de3ab","uuid":"dfa40f38-a8b6-4baf-9a7c-9caf8921e1fd"}
