{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01WnxMJZzzpCyaW7yLZWFUS7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_016CNMTAwDXdzzrp9jFwDT1g","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Fix all entity files column names","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"I need to fix the entity Java files to have the EXACT column names matching the original data.sql. The base path is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/woehlke/jakartaee/petclinic/\n\nThe original data.sql uses these exact column names (I'm listing the INSERT statements):\n\nOwner table \"owner\": id, address, address_info, city, email, first_name, housenumber, lastName, phonenumber, searchindex, uuid, zipcode\n\nPetType table \"owner_pet_pettype\": id, name, searchindex, uuid\n\nPet table \"owner_pet\": id, birth_date, name, searchindex, uuid, owner_id, owner_pet_pettype_id\n\nVisit table \"owner_pet_visit\": id, visit_date, description, searchindex, uuid, owner_pet_id\n\nSpecialty table \"specialty\": id, name, searchindex, uuid\n\nVet table \"vet\": id, first_name, lastName, searchindex, uuid\nJoin table \"vet_specialties\": vet_id, specialty_id\n\nPlease fix these files by reading each one and then writing the corrected version. The key fixes needed:\n\n1. **Pet.java** (pet/db/Pet.java):\n   - JoinColumn for type should be \"owner_pet_pettype_id\" (currently \"pettype_id\")\n   - Good: owner_id is correct, birth_date is correct\n\n2. **Vet.java** (vet/db/Vet.java):\n   - Column for lastName should be \"lastName\" (currently \"last_name\")\n   - first_name is correct\n   - vet_specialties join table is correct\n\n3. **Visit.java** (visit/db/Visit.java):\n   - Column for date should be \"visit_date\" (currently \"date\")\n   - JoinColumn for pet should be \"owner_pet_id\" (currently \"pet_id\")\n   - description is correct\n\n4. **PetType.java** (pettype/db/PetType.java) - verify it's correct (table \"owner_pet_pettype\", columns: id, name, searchindex, uuid)\n\n5. **Specialty.java** (specialty/db/Specialty.java) - verify it's correct (table \"specialty\", columns: id, name, searchindex, uuid)\n\n6. **Owner.java** (owner/db/Owner.java) - already fixed, skip this one\n\nFor each file that needs fixing, read it first using the Read tool, then write the corrected version using the Write tool. Only fix the column name annotations, keep everything else the same."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":447,"cache_read_input_tokens":138027,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":447,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":746},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f1542671-6929-49f9-9925-fcf6260de3ab","uuid":"09311c66-b56f-47d4-b771-40161efafb72"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need to fix the entity Java files to have the EXACT column names matching the original data.sql. The base path is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__jakarta__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/woehlke/jakartaee/petclinic/\n\nThe original data.sql uses these exact column names (I'm listing the INSERT statements):\n\nOwner table \"owner\": id, address, address_info, city, email, first_name, housenumber, lastName, phonenumber, searchindex, uuid, zipcode\n\nPetType table \"owner_pet_pettype\": id, name, searchindex, uuid\n\nPet table \"owner_pet\": id, birth_date, name, searchindex, uuid, owner_id, owner_pet_pettype_id\n\nVisit table \"owner_pet_visit\": id, visit_date, description, searchindex, uuid, owner_pet_id\n\nSpecialty table \"specialty\": id, name, searchindex, uuid\n\nVet table \"vet\": id, first_name, lastName, searchindex, uuid\nJoin table \"vet_specialties\": vet_id, specialty_id\n\nPlease fix these files by reading each one and then writing the corrected version. The key fixes needed:\n\n1. **Pet.java** (pet/db/Pet.java):\n   - JoinColumn for type should be \"owner_pet_pettype_id\" (currently \"pettype_id\")\n   - Good: owner_id is correct, birth_date is correct\n\n2. **Vet.java** (vet/db/Vet.java):\n   - Column for lastName should be \"lastName\" (currently \"last_name\")\n   - first_name is correct\n   - vet_specialties join table is correct\n\n3. **Visit.java** (visit/db/Visit.java):\n   - Column for date should be \"visit_date\" (currently \"date\")\n   - JoinColumn for pet should be \"owner_pet_id\" (currently \"pet_id\")\n   - description is correct\n\n4. **PetType.java** (pettype/db/PetType.java) - verify it's correct (table \"owner_pet_pettype\", columns: id, name, searchindex, uuid)\n\n5. **Specialty.java** (specialty/db/Specialty.java) - verify it's correct (table \"specialty\", columns: id, name, searchindex, uuid)\n\n6. **Owner.java** (owner/db/Owner.java) - already fixed, skip this one\n\nFor each file that needs fixing, read it first using the Read tool, then write the corrected version using the Write tool. Only fix the column name annotations, keep everything else the same."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016CNMTAwDXdzzrp9jFwDT1g","session_id":"f1542671-6929-49f9-9925-fcf6260de3ab","uuid":"ca440e70-9b84-4724-bf74-a0bd59aecd6a"}
