{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LAkt6gn2iWqvK4DaKJpWY8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.api;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty;\n     4→import lombok.*;\n     5→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pet.api.PetDto;\n     6→\n     7→import java.io.Serializable;\n     8→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Getter\n    13→@Setter\n    14→@ToString\n    15→@NoArgsConstructor\n    16→@AllArgsConstructor\n    17→public class OwnerDto implements Serializable {\n    18→\n    19→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    20→\n    21→    @JsonProperty(\"id\")\n    22→    private Long id;\n    23→\n    24→    @JsonProperty(\"uuid\")\n    25→    private UUID uuid;\n    26→\n    27→    @JsonProperty(\"firstName\")\n    28→    private String firstName;\n    29→\n    30→    @JsonProperty(\"lastName\")\n    31→    private String lastName;\n    32→\n    33→    @JsonProperty(\"address\")\n    34→    private String address;\n    35→\n    36→    @JsonProperty(\"houseNumber\")\n    37→    private String houseNumber;\n    38→\n    39→    @JsonProperty(\"addressInfo\")\n    40→    private String addressInfo;\n    41→\n    42→    @JsonProperty(\"city\")\n    43→    private String city;\n    44→\n    45→    @JsonProperty(\"zipCode\")\n    46→    private String zipCode;\n    47→\n    48→    @JsonProperty(\"phoneNumber\")\n    49→    private String phoneNumber;\n    50→\n    51→    @JsonProperty(\"petList\")\n    52→    private List<PetDto> petList = new ArrayList<>();\n    53→}\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer qu