{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01CuURdVEwso9c34V25Ccnpk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The root cause is clear: `column \"lastname\" of relation \"owner\" does not exist`. Hibernate is creating the column with a different name than what's in data.sql. The issue is that Hibernate's default naming strategy converts `lastName` (Java field) to `last_name` in the database, but the data.sql uses `lastName`. \n\nThis is a Hibernate naming strategy issue. The `@Column(name = \"lastName\")` annotation is being transformed by Hibernate's `ImplicitNamingStrategy` or `PhysicalNamingStrategy` to `last_name`. I need to configure Hibernate to use the column names exactly as specified."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3333,"cache_read_input_tokens":60171,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3333,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":254},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f1542671-6929-49f9-9925-fcf6260de3ab","uuid":"d86e3df9-8079-40c9-8c6e-f91c38bab9bb"}
