{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01R33A6xgjhmwu4RPbHJKckP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks are complete. Here's a summary of the migration:\n\n## Migration Complete: Jakarta EE 10 -> Spring Boot 3.2.5\n\n**What was done:**\n- Replaced the entire Jakarta EE 10 stack (EJB, JAX-RS, CDI, JSF/PrimeFaces, OpenLiberty) with Spring Boot 3.2.5\n- Created 41 Spring Boot Java files: entities, Spring Data JPA repositories, `@Service` + `@Transactional` services, `@RestController` controllers, DTOs, and converter utilities\n- Configured `PhysicalNamingStrategyStandardImpl` to preserve the original schema's mixed naming conventions (`lastName`, `housenumber`, `first_name`, etc.)\n- Updated the Dockerfile to build a Spring Boot fat JAR and run with `java -jar` instead of `mvn clean liberty:run`\n- Preserved all REST endpoints under `/petclinic/rest/` and all seed data\n\n**Key issue resolved:** Hibernate's default Spring Boot naming strategy was converting `@Column(name = \"lastName\")` to `last_name` in the generated DDL, causing data.sql INSERT failures. Fixed by setting `spring.jpa.hibernate.naming.physical-strategy=org.hibernate.boot.model.naming.PhysicalNamingStrategyStandardImpl`.\n\n**Smoke test results:** 17/17 passed (health check, all list/detail endpoints, data validation for correct counts and values)."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":415,"cache_read_input_tokens":75212,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":415,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":344},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f1542671-6929-49f9-9925-fcf6260de3ab","uuid":"b4ec7262-e27a-4955-bfe8-7e91f1f3ea9d"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":1954982,"duration_api_ms":2086870,"num_turns":106,"result":"All tasks are complete. Here's a summary of the migration:\n\n## Migration Complete: Jakarta EE 10 -> Spring Boot 3.2.5\n\n**What was done:**\n- Replaced the entire Jakarta EE 10 stack (EJB, JAX-RS, CDI, JSF/PrimeFaces, OpenLiberty) with Spring Boot 3.2.5\n- Created 41 Spring Boot Java files: entities, Spring Data JPA repositories, `@Service` + `@Transactional` services, `@RestController` controllers, DTOs, and converter utilities\n- Configured `PhysicalNamingStrategyStandardImpl` to preserve the original schema's mixed naming conventions (`lastName`, `housenumber`, `first_name`, etc.)\n- Updated the Dockerfile to build a Spring Boot fat JAR and run with `java -jar` instead of `mvn clean liberty:run`\n- Preserved all REST endpoints under `/petclinic/rest/` and all seed data\n\n**Key issue resolved:** Hibernate's default Spring Boot naming strategy was converting `@Column(name = \"lastName\")` to `last_name` in the generated DDL, causing data.sql INSERT failures. Fixed by setting `spring.jpa.hibernate.naming.physical-strategy=org.hibernate.boot.model.naming.PhysicalNamingStrategyStandardImpl`.\n\n**Smoke test results:** 17/17 passed (health check, all list/detail endpoints, data validation for correct counts and values).","session_id":"f1542671-6929-49f9-9925-fcf6260de3ab","total_cost_usd":25.959651739999973,"usage":{"input_tokens":109,"cache_creation_input_tokens":200410,"cache_read_input_tokens":9029787,"output_tokens":40516,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":200410}},"modelUsage":{"aws/claude-3-5-haiku":{"inputTokens":288186,"outputTokens":10832,"cacheReadInputTokens":274328,"cacheCreationInputTokens":44051,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.3398740399999997,"contextWindow":200000},"claude-sonnet-4-5-2025092